//Main Point of This Code

This solution uses a min heap of size k to find the kth largest element efficiently.

💡 Why a Min Heap for kth Largest?

To find the kth largest element:

We want to keep track of the k largest elements seen so far.

Among those k largest, the one we care about is the smallest of them
→ that is exactly the kth largest overall.

So we use a min heap of size k.